\begin_layout Standard
Karl Marx's analysis of the circuit of capital is one of the most important
 and pioneering accomplishments in the history of political economy.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
key "jiang2014endogenous"

\end_inset

 finds echoes of it in the work of such luminaries as Von Neumann (balanced
 growth), Leontief (input-output), Sraffa (circulating capital), and Walras
 (general equilibrium).
 It also is highly influential in heterodox theories of non-equilibrium
 dynamics 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "freeman1996marxand"

\end_inset

, the monetary circuit 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
before "e.g.,"
key "trigg2004marxand"

\end_inset

, and crises and financial instability 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "rugitsky2014financialization"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Outside economics, in economic geography and critical urban studies it has
 been extremely influential, largely through David Harvey's 
