\begin_layout Standard
This paper begins to fill a lacuna between heterodox economics and urban
 political economy.
 During the late 1970s these two fields of inquiry 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Over the past four decades the former has made great strides in understanding
 the macroeconomic dynamics of capitalism and its crises, whereas the latter
 has generated substantial insights into the spatial organization of human
 settlements under capitalism and its implications for capitalism's dynamics.
